parameters.name: Purpose
parameters.description:
indicates that this row contains science         
    data

parameters.name: SCLOCK
parameters.description:
start time of the averaging interval as a        
    spacecraft clock string; SCLOCK values are recorded as P/NNNNNNNNNN.FFF   
    where P is the partition number, NNNNNNNNNN is roughly the number of      
    seconds since the start of the partition, and FFF is the number of ticks. 
    Each tick is roughly 1/256 of a second.

parameters.name: Start_Ephemeris_s
parameters.description:
start time of the averaging interval in          
    ephemeris time (TDB seconds past the J2000 epoch)

parameters.name: End_Ephemeris_s
parameters.description:
end time of the averaging interval in            
    ephemeris time (TDB seconds past the J2000 epoch)

parameters.name: Ave_doy
parameters.description:
start of the hour-long averaging interval        
    expressed as a fractional day of year

parameters.name: Radial_Distance
parameters.description:
position of Cassini at start of one-hour         
	interval in Saturn radii, where 1 RS = 60268 km

parameters.name: Latitude
parameters.description:
latitude of Cassini at start of                  
    measurement in the SZS (Saturn Equatorial System) frame

parameters.name: Local_Time
parameters.description:
local time of Cassini at the start of the        
    measurement given in hours and in the SZS system
